PN,46602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F466A1776003065
OL,3,CMan avoids jail and still allowed to
OL,4,Cdrive after woman died in crash
OL,6,FA trial of facts was held in March by
OL,7,Fthe prosecution and a jury found
OL,8,FBayliss responsible for her death.
OL,10,FJudge Hudges told Newport Crown Court
OL,11,Ftoday (Thursday, 9 April) that Bayliss
OL,12,Fsustained significant injuries,
OL,13,Fincluding brain damage, which means he
OL,14,Fis now unable to work.
OL,16,FShe went on to explain that there were
OL,17,Fonly three sentencing options
OL,18,Favailable to her, due to the fact he
OL,19,Fwas unfit to stand trial, and gave him
OL,20,Fan absolute discharge.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/4
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
